reviewer_text: [{"reviewer_text":"It’s finally in Cebu. The taste gives me the nostalgia of the Binondo restos. Kinda pricey, but they serve proper chinese food. [{"reviewer_text":"A Taste of Mandarin has been my family's favorite go to Chinese restaurant for years now, however, the quality of their service has remarkably gone down.

name: Tea Of Spring - Shangri-la's Mactan Resort & Spa

reviewer_text:
[{"reviewer_text":"I had an ocular in Shang Mactan and this restaurant was said to be one of their bests so I gave it a try. Delicious food, staff were accommodating and generous servings."},{"reviewer_text":"What we had:
Sweet and sour soup, yang chow rice, roast chicken, pork knuckles, tiger prawn, chilled glutinous rice with mango filling

What I loved:
Great great Chinese food. For Shangri-La price, ToS I guess is most affordable. Serving is generous, but most of all the service was commendable. Very professional, accommodating, warm staff here. They change your plates as needed, and even offer to help with the prawn. (I have allergies to shrimp but the tiger prawn my friend had sure did look so delicious!) The roast chicken ang yang chow was so good! And the mochi-like dessert with fresh mangoes was a bonus.  🥰"}]

address: No. 8 Humabon Street, San Antonio Village, Apas, Lahug, Cebu City
reviewer_text:
[{"reviewer_text":"I've always loved this place! My go-to place everytime I crave for chicken wings.
Food is VERY good
Place is clean
But there are two things that I believe needs to be addressed for their service to improve more..

1. Comfort Room - their cr is not that clean, no water most of the time.
2. Lavatory - for you to be able to savor your chicken wings, you'd want to eat it with your hands. Their sink is Okay but can can definitely be improved. They use pail to catch the dirty water and the water will definitely hit your leg, which is something not pleasant to a customer."},{"reviewer_text":"The best chicken wings in town so far though it's not unli but was soo worth the price!! Cajun and plain mojos are definitely a must try !! 👍👍"}]

name: Coffee Project
address: Ground Floor, Starmall, Talisay City, Cebu
reviewer_text: [{"reviewer_text":"great ambience and great coffee"},{"reviewer_text":"We decided to have Coffee to stay away from the jampacked streets. It took a while for someone to take my order because there was only one barista but he asked if I could wait a little so that's fine. At least he was mindful of the customers. We got the Grande Cafe Americano and Sweet Cold Brew. Both tasted good and the price was okay. The cafe was artsy and had a relaxing atmosphere. The comfort room was clean and had everything you need (toilet paper, hand soap, paper towels, hand dryer). Right infront of the counter, they have an area with sugar, water, milk, trash can, etc. Overall, the cafe is a good place to gather for all occasions. Planning to visit again and try their meals."}]

name: Ding Qua Qua Dimsum House
address: Second Floor, JY Square Discovery Mall, Lahug, Cebu City
reviewer_text: [{"reviewer_text":"The place is always full when I go but the service is great. This is a great place to eat when hungry but on a budget. A Cebuano staple definitely!!"},{"reviewer_text":"Ding qua qua is a great dimsum place. It is famous for its affordable buffet and really good dimsum. I liked the quail egg dimsum, and the unli steam rice. The wide selection of food makes the buffet worth it - patatim, several dimsum, noodle soup, spring roll, and other meat, buchi, etc. It is good enough. Although i do not see servers most of the time, and ambience is like a typical cheao buffet resto."}]

reviewer_text:
[{"reviewer_text":"PLACE is good. Spacious. Love the seats and the interior as well. I love the atmosphere, family crowd and I’ve seen crowd of old people catching up.

SERVER was slow. This was the only problem we encountered. Our server was great don’t get me wrong. But the food was very slow. Everytime they put food in our table we finish eat and the next dish took time to be served. It was just frustrating especially when you are
